---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Career Companion" description="Privacy Policy for Career Companion app - how we collect, use, and safeguard your career data">
  <Header />

  <main id="main-content">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Privacy Policy for Career Companion</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          How we collect, use, and safeguard your career information
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
          <strong>Effective Date:</strong> January 1, 2026
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Career Companion ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application. Your career data is personal and sensitive, and we take its protection seriously.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Career Data</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>Meeting Data:</strong> 1:1 meeting information including agendas, notes, action items, and attendee details</li>
              <li><strong>Career Goals:</strong> Goal titles, descriptions, progress, milestones, and target dates</li>
              <li><strong>Achievements:</strong> Achievement records, impact statements, evidence links, and visibility settings</li>
              <li><strong>Action Items:</strong> Tasks, due dates, priorities, status, and owner assignments</li>
              <li><strong>People Data:</strong> Names, relationship types, and meeting history for managers, mentors, peers, and reports</li>
              <li><strong>Sentiment Data:</strong> Meeting and weekly sentiment ratings you choose to record</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Technical Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Basic device information for app functionality</li>
              <li><strong>iCloud Data:</strong> Career data synced through Apple's iCloud service</li>
              <li><strong>Calendar Data:</strong> Meeting events if you choose to enable calendar integration</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How We Collect Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>User Input:</strong> Information you enter when creating meetings, goals, and achievements</li>
              <li><strong>iCloud Sync:</strong> Automatic synchronization through Apple's CloudKit service</li>
              <li><strong>Calendar Integration:</strong> Meeting data from EventKit if you enable calendar sync</li>
              <li><strong>Siri:</strong> Voice commands if you use Siri Shortcuts</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Primary Uses</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>App Functionality:</strong> To provide career tracking, meeting management, and goal tracking services</li>
              <li><strong>Data Synchronization:</strong> To sync your career data across your devices via iCloud</li>
              <li><strong>Report Generation:</strong> To create performance reports for your personal use</li>
              <li><strong>AI Suggestions:</strong> To provide intelligent agenda suggestions (processed on-device only)</li>
              <li><strong>Widgets & Shortcuts:</strong> To display information in iOS widgets and respond to Siri commands</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Data Storage</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>CloudKit Private Database:</strong> All career data is stored in your personal iCloud account's private database</li>
              <li><strong>No Third-Party Storage:</strong> We do not store your data on our servers or any third-party services</li>
              <li><strong>Your Data, Your Control:</strong> Data is encrypted and accessible only to you through your iCloud account</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">We Do Not Share Your Data</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li>We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties</li>
              <li>We do not share your career data, meeting notes, or achievements with anyone</li>
              <li>Your data remains completely private and accessible only to you</li>
              <li>We cannot access your data stored in CloudKit's private database</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Export Features</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>User-Initiated Exports:</strong> You can export agendas to Slack, Teams, or email—this is entirely your choice</li>
              <li><strong>Data Backup:</strong> You can export your data to JSON/CSV for personal backup</li>
              <li><strong>Report Sharing:</strong> Performance reports can be shared at your discretion</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Apple Services</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>iCloud:</strong> Your career data syncs through Apple's iCloud service to your private database</li>
              <li><strong>App Store:</strong> Basic app analytics provided by Apple</li>
              <li><strong>EventKit:</strong> Calendar integration if you choose to enable it</li>
              <li><strong>StoreKit:</strong> In-app purchase processing for premium features</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Security</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Protection Measures</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>CloudKit Encryption:</strong> All data is encrypted using Apple's standard encryption in CloudKit</li>
              <li><strong>Private Database:</strong> Data is stored in CloudKit's private database, inaccessible to anyone but you</li>
              <li><strong>On-Device Processing:</strong> AI suggestions are processed entirely on your device</li>
              <li><strong>Device Security:</strong> Device-level security (Face ID, Touch ID, passcode) protects local data</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Your Responsibilities</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li>Keep your device and iCloud account secure</li>
              <li>Use strong passwords for your Apple ID</li>
              <li>Enable two-factor authentication for additional security</li>
              <li>Be mindful when sharing exported reports or agendas</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Access and Control</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4">
              <li><strong>View Your Data:</strong> All career data is visible and searchable within the app</li>
              <li><strong>Edit Data:</strong> You can edit or update any information at any time</li>
              <li><strong>Delete Data:</strong> You can delete individual items or all data through the app</li>
              <li><strong>Export Data:</strong> Full data export available in JSON and CSV formats</li>
              <li><strong>iCloud Control:</strong> Manage iCloud sync through your device settings</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Opt-Out Options</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Disable iCloud Sync:</strong> Turn off iCloud sync in device settings</li>
              <li><strong>Calendar Integration:</strong> Disable calendar sync in app settings</li>
              <li><strong>AI Suggestions:</strong> Disable AI features in app settings</li>
              <li><strong>Demo Mode:</strong> Use demo mode to explore without storing real data</li>
              <li><strong>Delete App:</strong> Removing the app removes local data; iCloud data can be managed separately</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Premium Features</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              Career Companion offers premium features through in-app purchase. Premium features are processed through Apple's StoreKit:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li>We do not receive or store your payment information</li>
              <li>All transactions are handled by Apple</li>
              <li>We only receive confirmation of purchase status</li>
              <li>Restore purchases functionality is available for account recovery</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Career Companion is designed for professional use and is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">International Users</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              If you are using our app outside the United Kingdom, please note that your information is stored in your personal iCloud account, which is managed by Apple according to their data residency policies. Apple maintains data centers in multiple regions to comply with local data protection requirements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li>Posting the new Privacy Policy in the app</li>
              <li>Updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this policy</li>
              <li>App Store update notes when significant changes occur</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact Information</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:dev@camilopires.co.uk" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">dev@camilopires.co.uk</a><br>
                <strong>Developer:</strong> Camilo Pires
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Compliance</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              This Privacy Policy complies with:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>App Store Guidelines:</strong> Apple's App Store Review Guidelines</li>
              <li><strong>GDPR:</strong> General Data Protection Regulation (for EU users, including UK)</li>
              <li><strong>UK Data Protection Act 2018:</strong> UK data protection legislation</li>
              <li><strong>CCPA:</strong> California Consumer Privacy Act (for California users)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-600 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>iCloud Data:</strong> Stored in your iCloud account until you delete it</li>
              <li><strong>Backup Data:</strong> Subject to your device's backup settings</li>
              <li><strong>Deleted Data:</strong> Permanently removed from CloudKit when deleted through the app</li>
              <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> All data removed if you delete your iCloud account</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="border-t pt-8 mt-8">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
              This Privacy Policy is effective as of the date listed above and applies to all users of the Career Companion app. Your privacy matters—your career data stays yours.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Back to Project -->
  <section class="py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <a href="/projects/careercompanion" class="inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-semibold">
        ← Back to Career Companion Project
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
